  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your total load is fine — it's the sameness that needs fixing. Your 7-day average strain of 11.9 is essentially at your 30-day norm of 12.1, so volume isn't the problem, but your monotony score is 2.4, firmly in the flagged zone: nearly every day lands at the same moderate intensity. The fix is polarizing, not cutting. Keep the week's volume, but make one session genuinely hard, drop two others to conversational easy pace, and take one full rest day. Same fitness stimulus, more variation for your body to adapt around — your aerobic goal stays on track, just with a healthier weekly shape.",
